---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy | ComplyEaze Tools"
  description="Privacy posture for ComplyEaze Tools: browser-local tool input handling, static hosting metadata, and Cloudflare security checks."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div>
      <h1>Browser-local by design.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Tool files are processed in your browser and are not uploaded by the
        tool. The site may still receive ordinary request metadata while serving
        static pages and assets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="detail-grid" aria-label="Privacy commitments">
    <article>
      <h2>What stays local</h2>
      <p>
        Pasted rows, review text, generated drafts, and downloaded text files are
        handled by code running in your browser. The V0 tools do not create
        accounts, upload files, call an application API, or send tool input to
        ComplyEaze.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>What hosting may see</h2>
      <p>
        Static hosting, ingress, certificate, and security systems may process
        ordinary web request metadata such as IP address, user agent, request
        path, timestamp, and TLS details while serving pages and assets.
        Operational access to these logs should be limited to deployment,
        security, abuse-prevention, cache, and troubleshooting work. They are
        not product analytics and are not intended to reconstruct pasted rows,
        generated drafts, or downloaded artifact contents.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Cloudflare security checks</h2>
      <p>
        The public host may use Cloudflare security features, including
        JavaScript Detections or challenge scripts served from
        /cdn-cgi/challenge-platform, to evaluate automated traffic. Those
        systems may set Cloudflare cookies such as cf_clearance and process
        browser/security signals, challenge outcomes, Ray IDs, and request
        metadata under Cloudflare's product controls and retention settings.
        They are not part of the tool workbench; the tool code must not
        intentionally send pasted tool rows or generated drafts to ComplyEaze or
        Cloudflare.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>What not to paste</h2>
      <p>
        Do not paste real credentials, OTPs, CAPTCHA answers, GSTINs, Aadhaar
        numbers, bank details, portal cookies, portal screenshots, full notices,
        ledgers, or taxpayer documents into public issues, screenshots,
        fixtures, or support threads.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Professional review</h2>
      <p>
        Outputs are drafts for review. Verify source documents, dates, amounts,
        identities, and statutory positions before sending anything to a client,
        counterparty, portal, authority, or auditor.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
